occurs when the fetus cannot enter or advance 
through the birth canal despite sustained 
labor contractions. Without access to C-section, 
women with obstructed labor have a high 
risk of death at delivery, postpartum sepsis, or 
obstetric fistulas (one of the most devastating 
birth injuries). Lack of access to C-sections 
can also adversely affect perinatal outcomes.
